# Configuration for the Claude Remote daemon systemd user service.
#
# scripts/install-service.sh copies this file to
#   ~/.config/claude-remote/daemon.env
# on first install (it never overwrites an existing copy). Edit that copy and
# then restart the service:
#
#   systemctl --user restart claude-remote
#
# Lines are plain KEY=VALUE pairs read by systemd's EnvironmentFile. No shell
# quoting, no `export`, no inline comments after a value.

# Address the WebSocket server binds to. 0.0.0.0 accepts connections from any
# interface on the LAN (the intended setup). Use 127.0.0.1 to restrict the
# daemon to this machine, e.g. when reaching it only over a WireGuard tunnel
# terminated locally.
BIND=0.0.0.0

# WebSocket port the phone connects to. Must match the port configured in the
# Android app and advertised over mDNS.
PORT=8770

# Extra flags appended to the daemon command line, split on whitespace.
# Common choices:
#   -v             info-level logging  (-vv for debug)
#   --require-auth reject any device that has not completed pairing
# Leave empty for the quiet, accept-any-token dev default.
EXTRA_ARGS=-v

# --- Spawning claude under systemd --------------------------------------------
# A systemd user service runs with a minimal PATH (no ~/.local/bin, pnpm, pyenv
# shims, ...). install-service.sh auto-fills the two keys below from your shell
# at install time; they are shown here for reference. If sessions fail with
# "failed to spawn [claude]", set CLAUDE_REMOTE_CLAUDE_CMD by hand and restart.
#
# Absolute path to the claude binary (avoids relying on PATH to find it):
# CLAUDE_REMOTE_CLAUDE_CMD=/home/you/.local/bin/claude
#
# PATH for the daemon and the claude sessions it spawns (they inherit it), so
# claude and your tools resolve. Include your tool dirs:
# PATH=/home/you/.local/bin:/usr/local/bin:/usr/bin:/bin:/snap/bin
